                <h1 class="font-bold text-center">The few rules of <span class="text-java-pink font-black">I Love Java</span> are <span class="text-java-blue font-black">simple</span>!</h1>
                <div class="lg:max-w-[66%] my-16 text-5xl lg:text-2xl font-normal tracking-tight break-words mx-auto">
                    <p class="text-6xl lg:text-3xl text-center"> To create a positive and collaborative community, we rely on everyone's participation and adherence to these simple rules.
                    </p><br>
                    <!--  TODO : add a space between each rule, maybe add a vertical bar on the left side of the rules too  -->
                    <div class="mx-auto text-left">
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">1.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Keep discussions on topic.</span> The forum is for discussing Java programming and related topics. Off-topic discussions should be avoided.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">2.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Be respectful and courteous to other members.</span> Disagreements and debates are fine, but personal attacks and rude behavior will not be tolerated.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">3.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">No spam or self-promotion.</span> Do not use the forum to promote your own products or services, or to spam links to external websites.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">4.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">No illegal or inappropriate content.</span> Do not post content that is illegal copyrighted, or otherwise inappropriate.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">5.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Keep discussions constructive.</span> The purpose of the forum is to help members learn and improve their Java programming skills. Posts that do not contribute to this goal, such as overly negative or unhelpful, should be avoided.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">6.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Use proper formatting and language.</span> Posts should be written in clear and concise language, and should use proper formatting to make them easy to read, you can use the <a class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-4 decoration-java-blue/80 break-keep block lg:inline-block" href="https://www.markdownguide.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Markdown features</a> to this end.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">7.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Do not ask for homework help.</span> The forum is not a place to receive free help with homework assignments. Instead, try to figure out the solution on your own and ask for help if you get stuck.
                        </p>
                        <p class="py-8"><span class="font-black text-java-blue">8.</span> <span class="font-bold text-java-blue">Follow the rules of the forum.</span> Make sure to familiarize yourself with the full set of rules for the forum and abide by them at all times.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <br>
